.TH PRETTY_FILES 1 "July 2026" "pretty_files 1.3.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
pretty_files \- lightweight command-line file viewer with syntax highlighting

.SH SYNOPSIS

.B pretty_files
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <PATHS...>

.br

.B pretty_files
.B bare
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <DIRECTORIES...>

.br

.B pretty_files
.B help

.br

.B pretty_files
.B binary

.SH DESCRIPTION

.B pretty_files
is a lightweight command-line file viewer written in Rust.
It displays files with syntax highlighting, optional line numbers,
and recursive directory traversal.

Files are automatically detected by their extension.
Unsupported file types are displayed as plain text.

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B help
Display the general help menu.

.TP
.B bare
List file paths instead of displaying file contents.
Useful for piping file lists into other commands.

.TP
.B binary
View binary files.
This feature is currently not implemented.

.SH READ MODE

Read mode is the default mode.
It displays the contents of one or more files.

.SS Options

.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-numbers
Display line numbers before each line.

.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-recursive
Recursively search directories and display all discovered files.

.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Display file names before their contents.

.TP
.B \-D
Disable automatic debug mode.

Automatic debug mode is enabled when multiple files are displayed.

.TP
.B \-S
Disable syntax highlighting.

.SS Examples

.TP
Display a file:
.B pretty_files main.rs

.TP
Display multiple files:
.B pretty_files main.rs Cargo.toml

.TP
Display with line numbers:
.B pretty_files -n main.rs

.TP
Display all files in a directory recursively:
.B pretty_files -r src/

.TP
Disable syntax highlighting:
.B pretty_files -S file.txt


.SH BARE MODE

The
.B bare
command prints file paths without reading file contents.

.SS Synopsis

.B pretty_files bare
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <DIRECTORIES...>

.SS Options

.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-recursive
Recursively search directories and print all discovered files.

.SS Examples

.TP
List files in a directory:
.B pretty_files bare src/

.TP
List files recursively:
.B pretty_files bare -r src/

.TP
Use output in a shell loop:
.nf
for file in $(pretty_files bare -r src/); do
    cat "$file"
done
.fi


.SH BINARY MODE

The
.B binary
command is reserved for future binary file support.

.SH NOTES

.TP
Automatic debug mode is enabled when displaying multiple files.
Use
.B \-D
to disable it.

.TP
The
.B \-r
option expects directories as input.

.TP
Files with unknown extensions are displayed as plain text.

.SH DEPENDENCIES

.TP
.B syntect
Provides syntax highlighting and language detection.

.TP
.B walkdir
Provides recursive directory traversal.

